original: Danielson, Axel Otto, landsfogde, Kalmar, f. 21/2/05 i Luleå av not. i järnv:styr. Johan Otto D. o. Märta Lilja. G. m. Anna Berit Kihl. Barn: Margareta f. 41, Berit 45. — Stud:ex. v. södra latin i Sthlm 23, jur. kand. i Sthlm 28. Tingstjg. i Östersysslets doms., anst. v. länsstyr. i Sthlms 1., landsfogde i Norrb. 1. 37, t. f. landsfogde i Kalm. 1. sed. 47. RNO, FFrK-4kl, MM f. hum. verksamh. und. Finl. krig 41-44.
translated: Danielson, Axel Otto, district governor, Kalmar, born on February 21, 1905 in Luleå to a railroad controller named Johan Otto D. and Märta Lilja. Married to Anna Berit Kihl in the year 19xx. Children: Margareta born in 1941, Berit born in 1945. Graduated from Södra Latin in Stockholm in 1923, became a law graduate in Stockholm in 1928. Served as a magistrate in the Östersysslets district court, employed by the county government of Stockholm for one year, district governor in Norrbotten from 1937, acting district governor in Kalmar since 1947. Awarded the Royal Order of the North Star, the Knight's Cross of the Order of the Sword, and the Medal of Military Merit for his humanitarian work during the Finnish War from 1941-44.
